 61  /** 
 62   * The root namespace for OpenSeadragon, this function also serves as a single
 63   * point of instantiation for an {@link OpenSeadragon.Viewer}, including all 
 64   * combinations of out-of-the-box configurable features.  All utility methods 
 65   * and classes are defined on or below this namespace. 
 66   *
 67   * @namespace
 68   * @function
 69   * @name OpenSeadragon
 70   * @exports $ as OpenSeadragon
 71   *
 72   * @param {Object} options All required and optional settings for instantiating
 73   *     a new instance of an OpenSeadragon image viewer. 
 74   *
 75   * @param {String} options.xmlPath 
 76   *     DEPRECATED. A relative path to load a DZI file from the server. 
 77   *     Prefer the newer options.tileSources.
 78   *
 79   * @param {Array|String|Function|Object[]|Array[]|String[]|Function[]} options.tileSources
 80   *     As an Array, the tileSource can hold either be all Objects or mixed 
 81   *     types of Arrays of Objects, String, Function. When a value is a String, 
 82   *     the tileSource is used to create a {@link OpenSeadragon.DziTileSource}.  
 83   *     When a value is a Function, the function is used to create a new 
 84   *     {@link OpenSeadragon.TileSource} whose abstract method 
 85   *     getUrl( level, x, y ) is implemented by the function. Finally, when it 
 86   *     is an Array of objects, it is used to create a 
 87   *     {@link OpenSeadragon.LegacyTileSource}.
 88   *
 89   * @param {Boolean} [options.debugMode=true]
 90   *     Currently does nothing. TODO: provide an in-screen panel providing event
 91   *     detail feedback.
 92   *
 93   * @param {Number} [options.animationTime=1.5]
 94   *     Specifies the animation duration per each {@link OpenSeadragon.Spring}
 95   *     which occur when the image is dragged or zoomed.
 96   *
 97   * @param {Number} [options.blendTime=0.5] 
 98   *     Specifies the duration of animation as higher or lower level tiles are
 99   *     replacing the existing tile.
100   *
101   * @param {Boolean} [options.alwaysBlend=false]
102   *     Forces the tile to always blend.  By default the tiles skip blending
103   *     when the blendTime is surpassed and the current animation frame would
104   *     not complete the blend.
105   *
106   * @param {Boolean} [options.autoHideControls=true]
107   *     If the user stops interacting with the viewport, fade the navigation 
108   *     controls.  Useful for presentation since the controls are by default
109   *     floated on top of the image the user is viewing.
110   *
111   * @param {Boolean} [options.immediateRender=false]
112   *     Render the best closest level first, ignoring the lowering levels which
113   *     provide the effect of very blurry to sharp. It is recommended to change 
114   *     setting to true for mobile devices.
115   *
116   * @param {Boolean} [options.wrapHorizontal=false]
117   *     Set to true to force the image to wrap horizontally within the viewport.
118   *     Useful for maps or images representing the surface of a sphere or cylinder.
119   *
120   * @param {Boolean} [options.wrapVertical=false]
121   *     Set to true to force the image to wrap vertically within the viewport.
122   *     Useful for maps or images representing the surface of a sphere or cylinder.
123   *
124   * @param {Number} [options.minZoomImageRatio=0.8]
125   *     The minimum percentage ( expressed as a number between 0 and 1 ) of 
126   *     the viewport height or width at which the zoom out will be constrained.
127   *     Setting it to 0, for example will allow you to zoom out infinitly.
128   *
129   * @param {Number} [options.maxZoomPixelRatio=2]
130   *     The maximum ratio to allow a zoom-in to affect the highest level pixel
131   *     ratio. This can be set to Infinity to allow 'infinite' zooming into the
132   *     image though it is less effective visually if the HTML5 Canvas is not 
133   *     availble on the viewing device.
134   *
135   * @param {Number} [options.visibilityRatio=0.5]
136   *     The percentage ( as a number from 0 to 1 ) of the source image which
137   *     must be kept within the viewport.  If the image is dragged beyond that
138   *     limit, it will 'bounce' back until the minimum visibility ration is 
139   *     achieved.  Setting this to 0 and wrapHorizontal ( or wrapVertical ) to
140   *     true will provide the effect of an infinitely scrolling viewport.
141   *
142   * @param {Number} [options.springStiffness=5.0]
143   *
144   * @param {Number} [options.imageLoaderLimit=0]
145   *     The maximum number of image requests to make concurrently.  By default
146   *     it is set to 0 allowing the browser to make the maximum number of
147   *     image requests in parallel as allowed by the browsers policy.
148   *
149   * @param {Number} [options.clickTimeThreshold=200]
150   *     If multiple mouse clicks occurs within less than this number of 
151   *     milliseconds, treat them as a single click.
152   *
153   * @param {Number} [options.clickDistThreshold=5]
154   *     If a mouse or touch drag occurs and the distance to the starting drag
155   *     point is less than this many pixels, ignore the drag event.
156   *
157   * @param {Number} [options.zoomPerClick=2.0]
158   *     The "zoom distance" per mouse click or touch tap.
159   *
160   * @param {Number} [options.zoomPerScroll=1.2]
161   *     The "zoom distance" per mouse scroll or touch pinch.
162   *
163   * @param {Number} [options.zoomPerSecond=2.0]
164   *     The number of seconds to animate a single zoom event over.
165   *
166   * @param {Boolean} [options.showNavigationControl=true]
167   *     Set to false to prevent the appearance of the default navigation controls.
168   *
169   * @param {Number} [options.controlsFadeDelay=2000]
170   *     The number of milliseconds to wait once the user has stopped interacting
171   *     with the interface before begining to fade the controls. Assumes
172   *     showNavigationControl and autoHideControls are both true.
173   *
174   * @param {Number} [options.controlsFadeLength=1500]
175   *     The number of milliseconds to animate the controls fading out.
176   *
177   * @param {Number} [options.maxImageCacheCount=100]
178   *     The max number of images we should keep in memory (per drawer).
179   *
180   * @param {Number} [options.minPixelRatio=0.5]
181   *     The higher the minPixelRatio, the lower the quality of the image that
182   *     is considered sufficient to stop rendering a given zoom level.  For
183   *     example, if you are targeting mobile devices with less bandwith you may 
184   *     try setting this to 1.5 or higher.
185   *
186   * @param {Boolean} [options.mouseNavEnabled=true]
187   *     Is the user able to interact with the image via mouse or touch. Default 
188   *     interactions include draging the image in a plane, and zooming in toward
189   *     and away from the image.
190   *
191   * @param {String} [options.prefixUrl='']
192   *     Appends the prefixUrl to navImages paths, which is very useful
193   *     since the default paths are rarely useful for production
194   *     environments.
195   *
196   * @param {Object} [options.navImages=]
197   *     An object with a property for each button or other built-in navigation
198   *     control, eg the current 'zoomIn', 'zoomOut', 'home', and 'fullpage'.
199   *     Each of those in turn provides an image path for each state of the botton
200   *     or navigation control, eg 'REST', 'GROUP', 'HOVER', 'PRESS'. Finally the
201   *     image paths, by default assume there is a folder on the servers root path
202   *     called '/images', eg '/images/zoomin_rest.png'.  If you need to adjust
203   *     these paths, prefer setting the option.prefixUrl rather than overriding 
204   *     every image path directly through this setting.
205   *
206   * @returns {OpenSeadragon.Viewer}
207   */
208 OpenSeadragon = window.OpenSeadragon || function( options ){
209     
210     return new OpenSeadragon.Viewer( options );
211 
212 };

288     /**
289      * Taken from jQuery 1.6.1
290      * @name $.isPlainObject
291      * @function
292      * @see <a href='http://www.jquery.com/'>jQuery</a>
293      */
294     $.isPlainObject = function( obj ) {
295         // Must be an Object.
296         // Because of IE, we also have to check the presence of the constructor property.
297         // Make sure that DOM nodes and window objects don't pass through, as well
298         if ( !obj || OpenSeadragon.type(obj) !== "object" || obj.nodeType || $.isWindow( obj ) ) {
299             return false;
300         }
301 
302         // Not own constructor property must be Object
303         if ( obj.constructor &&
304             !hasOwn.call(obj, "constructor") &&
305             !hasOwn.call(obj.constructor.prototype, "isPrototypeOf") ) {
306             return false;
307         }
308 
309         // Own properties are enumerated firstly, so to speed up,
310         // if last one is own, then all properties are own.
311 
312         var key;
313         for ( key in obj ) {}
314 
315         return key === undefined || hasOwn.call( obj, key );
316     };

326         for ( var name in obj ) {
327             return false;
328         }
329         return true;

337  *  namespace.  Many, if not most, are taked directly from jQuery for use
338  *  to simplify and reduce common programming patterns.  More static methods 
339  *  from jQuery may eventually make their way into this though we are
340  *  attempting to avoid substaintial plagarism or the more explicit dependency
341  *  on jQuery only because OpenSeadragon is a broadly useful code base and
342  *  would be made less broad by requiring jQuery fully.
343  *
344  *  Some static methods have also been refactored from the original OpenSeadragon

349     /**
350      * Taken from jQuery 1.6.1
351      * @see <a href='http://www.jquery.com/'>jQuery</a>
352      */
353     $.extend = function() {
354         var options, 
355             name, 
356             src, 
357             copy, 
358             copyIsArray, 
359             clone,
360             target  = arguments[ 0 ] || {},
361             length  = arguments.length,
362             deep    = false,
363             i       = 1;
364 
365         // Handle a deep copy situation
366         if ( typeof target === "boolean" ) {
367             deep    = target;
368             target  = arguments[ 1 ] || {};
369             // skip the boolean and the target
370             i = 2;
371         }
372 
373         // Handle case when target is a string or something (possible in deep copy)
374         if ( typeof target !== "object" && !OpenSeadragon.isFunction( target ) ) {
375             target = {};
376         }
377 
378         // extend jQuery itself if only one argument is passed
379         if ( length === i ) {
380             target = this;
381             --i;
382         }
383 
384         for ( ; i < length; i++ ) {
385             // Only deal with non-null/undefined values
386             if ( ( options = arguments[ i ] ) != null ) {
387                 // Extend the base object
388                 for ( name in options ) {
389                     src = target[ name ];
390                     copy = options[ name ];
391 
392                     // Prevent never-ending loop
393                     if ( target === copy ) {
394                         continue;
395                     }
396 
397                     // Recurse if we're merging plain objects or arrays
398                     if ( deep && copy && ( OpenSeadragon.isPlainObject( copy ) || ( copyIsArray = OpenSeadragon.isArray( copy ) ) ) ) {
399                         if ( copyIsArray ) {
400                             copyIsArray = false;
401                             clone = src && OpenSeadragon.isArray( src ) ? src : [];
402 
403                         } else {
404                             clone = src && OpenSeadragon.isPlainObject( src ) ? src : {};
405                         }
406 
407                         // Never move original objects, clone them
408                         target[ name ] = OpenSeadragon.extend( deep, clone, copy );
409 
410                     // Don't bring in undefined values
411                     } else if ( copy !== undefined ) {
412                         target[ name ] = copy;
413                     }
414                 }
415             }
416         }
417 
418         // Return the modified object
419         return target;
420     };

531         /**
532          * Returns a DOM Element for the given id or element.
533          * @function
534          * @name OpenSeadragon.getElement
535          * @param {String|Element} element Accepts an id or element.
536          * @returns {Element} The element with the given id, null, or the element itself.
537          */
538         getElement: function( element ) { 
539             if ( typeof ( element ) == "string" ) {
540                 element = document.getElementById( element );
541             }
542             return element;
543         },

546         /**
547          * Determines the position of the upper-left corner of the element.
548          * @function
549          * @name OpenSeadragon.getElementPosition
550          * @param {Element|String} element - the elemenet we want the position for.
551          * @returns {Point} - the position of the upper left corner of the element. 
552          */
553         getElementPosition: function( element ) {
554             var result = new $.Point(),
555                 isFixed,
556                 offsetParent;
557 
558             element      = $.getElement( element );
559             isFixed      = $.getElementStyle( element ).position == "fixed";
560             offsetParent = getOffsetParent( element, isFixed );
561 
562             while ( offsetParent ) {
563 
564                 result.x += element.offsetLeft;
565                 result.y += element.offsetTop;
566 
567                 if ( isFixed ) {
568                     result = result.plus( $.getPageScroll() );
569                 }
570 
571                 element = offsetParent;
572                 isFixed = $.getElementStyle( element ).position == "fixed";
573                 offsetParent = getOffsetParent( element, isFixed );
574             }
575 
576             return result;
577         },
578

631         /**
632          * Gets the position of the mouse on the screen for a given event.
633          * @function
634          * @name OpenSeadragon.getMousePosition
635          * @param {Event} [event]
636          * @returns {Point}
637          */
638         getMousePosition: function( event ) {
639             var result = new $.Point();
640 
641             event = $.getEvent( event );
642 
643             if ( typeof( event.pageX ) == "number" ) {
644                 result.x = event.pageX;
645                 result.y = event.pageY;
646             } else if ( typeof( event.clientX ) == "number" ) {
647                 result.x = 
648                     event.clientX + 
649                     document.body.scrollLeft + 
650                     document.documentElement.scrollLeft;
651                 result.y = 
652                     event.clientY + 
653                     document.body.scrollTop + 
654                     document.documentElement.scrollTop;
655             } else {
656                 throw new Error(
657                     "Unknown event mouse position, no known technique."
658                 );
659             }
660 
661             return result;
662         },
663 
664 
665         /**
666          * Determines the pages current scroll position.
667          * @function
668          * @name OpenSeadragon.getPageScroll
669          * @returns {Point}
670          */
671         getPageScroll: function() {
672             var result  = new $.Point(),
673                 docElement = document.documentElement || {},
674                 body    = document.body || {};
675 
676             if ( typeof( window.pageXOffset ) == "number" ) {
677                 result.x = window.pageXOffset;
678                 result.y = window.pageYOffset;
679             } else if ( body.scrollLeft || body.scrollTop ) {
680                 result.x = body.scrollLeft;
681                 result.y = body.scrollTop;
682             } else if ( docElement.scrollLeft || docElement.scrollTop ) {
683                 result.x = docElement.scrollLeft;
684                 result.y = docElement.scrollTop;
685             }
686 
687             return result;
688         },

691         /**
692          * Determines the size of the browsers window.
693          * @function
694          * @name OpenSeadragon.getWindowSize
695          * @returns {Point}
696          */
697         getWindowSize: function() {
698             var result  = new $.Point(),
699                 docElement = document.documentElement || {},
700                 body    = document.body || {};
701 
702             if ( typeof( window.innerWidth ) == 'number' ) {
703                 result.x = window.innerWidth;

1029         /**
1030          * Makes an AJAX request.
1031          * @function
1032          * @name OpenSeadragon.makeAjaxRequest
1033          * @param {String} url - the url to request 
1034          * @param {Function} [callback] - a function to call when complete
1035          * @throws {Error}
1036          */
1037         makeAjaxRequest: function( url, callback ) {
1038             var async   = typeof( callback ) == "function",
1039                 request = null,
1040                 actual,
1041                 i;
1042 
1043             if ( async ) {
1044                 actual = callback;
1045                 callback = function() {
1046                     window.setTimeout(
1047                         $.createCallback( null, actual, request ), 
1048                         1
1049                     );
1050                 };
1051             }
1052 
1053             if ( window.ActiveXObject ) {
1054                 //TODO: very bad...Why check every time using try/catch when
1055                 //      we could determine once at startup which activeX object
1056                 //      was supported.  This will have significant impact on 
1057                 //      performance for IE Browsers
1058                 for ( i = 0; i < ACTIVEX.length; i++ ) {
1059                     try {
1060                         request = new ActiveXObject( ACTIVEX[ i ] );
1061                         break;
1062                     } catch (e) {
1063                         continue;
1064                     }
1065                 }
1066             } else if ( window.XMLHttpRequest ) {
1067                 request = new XMLHttpRequest();
1068             }
1069 
1070             if ( !request ) {
1071                 throw new Error( "Browser doesn't support XMLHttpRequest." );
1072             }
1073 
1074 
1075             if ( async ) {
1076                 /** @ignore */
1077                 request.onreadystatechange = function() {
1078                     if ( request.readyState == 4) {
1079                         request.onreadystatechange = new function() { };
1080                         callback();
1081                     }
1082                 };
1083             }
1084 
1085             try {
1086                 request.open( "GET", url, async );
1087                 request.send( null );
1088             } catch (e) {
1089                 $.console.log(
1090                     "%s while making AJAX request: %s",
1091                     e.name, 
1092                     e.message
1093                 );
1094 
1095                 request.onreadystatechange = null;
1096                 request = null;
1097 
1098                 if ( async ) {
1099                     callback();
1100                 }
1101             }
1102 
1103             return async ? null : request;
1104         },

1107         /**
1108          * Loads a Deep Zoom Image description from a url or XML string and
1109          * provides a callback hook for the resulting Document
1110          * @function
1111          * @name OpenSeadragon.createFromDZI
1112          * @param {String} xmlUrl
1113          * @param {String} xmlString
1114          * @param {Function} callback
1115          */
1116         createFromDZI: function( dzi, callback ) {
1117             var async       = typeof ( callback ) == "function",
1118                 xmlUrl      = dzi.substring(0,1) != '<' ? dzi : null,
1119                 xmlString   = xmlUrl ? null : dzi,

1125 
1126

1129                 filename = urlParts[ urlParts.length - 1 ];
1130                 lastDot  = filename.lastIndexOf( '.' );
1131

1134                 }

1137             }

1139             function finish( func, obj ) {
1140                 try {
1141                     return func( obj, tilesUrl );

1144                         return null;
1145                     } else {
1146                         throw e;
1147                     }
1148                 }
1149             }
1150

1153                     window.setTimeout( function() {
1154                         var source = finish( processDZIXml, parseXml( xmlString ) );
1155                         // call after finish sets error
1156                         callback( source, error );

1160                         var source = finish( processDZIResponse, xhr );
1161                         // call after finish sets error
1162                         callback( source, error );
1163                     });
1164                 }
1165

1167             }
1168 
1169             if ( xmlString ) {
1170                 return finish( 
1171                     processDZIXml,
1172                     parseXml( xmlString ) 
1173                 );
1174             } else {
1175                 return finish( 
1176                     processDZIResponse, 
1177                     $.makeAjaxRequest( xmlUrl )
1178                 );
1179             }
1180         }

1185     /**
1186      * The current browser vendor, version, and related information regarding
1187      * detected features.  Features include <br/>
1188      *  <strong>'alpha'</strong> - Does the browser support image alpha 
1189      *  transparency.<br/>
1190      * @name $.Browser
1191      * @static
1192      */
1193     $.Browser = {
1194         vendor:     $.BROWSERS.UNKNOWN,
1195         version:    0,
1196         alpha:      true
1197     };
1198 
1199 
1200     var ACTIVEX = [
1201             "Msxml2.XMLHTTP", 
1202             "Msxml3.XMLHTTP", 
1203             "Microsoft.XMLHTTP"
1204         ],  
1205         FILEFORMATS = {
1206             "bmp":  false,
1207             "jpeg": true,
1208             "jpg":  true,
1209             "png":  true,
1210             "tif":  false,
1211             "wdp":  false
1212         },
1213         URLPARAMS = {};
1214 
1215     (function() {
1216         //A small auto-executing routine to determine the browser vendor, 
1217         //version and supporting feature sets.
1218         var app = navigator.appName,
1219             ver = navigator.appVersion,
1220             ua  = navigator.userAgent;
1221 
1222         //console.error( 'appName: ' + navigator.appName );
1223         //console.error( 'appVersion: ' + navigator.appVersion );
1224         //console.error( 'userAgent: ' + navigator.userAgent );
1225 
1226         switch( navigator.appName ){
1227             case "Microsoft Internet Explorer":
1228                 if( !!window.attachEvent && 
1229                     !!window.ActiveXObject ) {
1230 
1231                     $.Browser.vendor = $.BROWSERS.IE;
1232                     $.Browser.version = parseFloat(
1233                         ua.substring( 
1234                             ua.indexOf( "MSIE" ) + 5, 
1235                             ua.indexOf( ";", ua.indexOf( "MSIE" ) ) )
1236                         );
1237                 }
1238                 break;
1239             case "Netscape":
1240                 if( !!window.addEventListener ){
1241                     if ( ua.indexOf( "Firefox" ) >= 0 ) {
1242                         $.Browser.vendor = $.BROWSERS.FIREFOX;
1243                         $.Browser.version = parseFloat(
1244                             ua.substring( ua.indexOf( "Firefox" ) + 8 )
1245                         );
1246                     } else if ( ua.indexOf( "Safari" ) >= 0 ) {
1247                         $.Browser.vendor = ua.indexOf( "Chrome" ) >= 0 ? 
1248                             $.BROWSERS.CHROME : 
1249                             $.BROWSERS.SAFARI;
1250                         $.Browser.version = parseFloat(
1251                             ua.substring( 
1252                                 ua.substring( 0, ua.indexOf( "Safari" ) ).lastIndexOf( "/" ) + 1, 
1253                                 ua.indexOf( "Safari" )
1254                             )
1255                         );
1256                     }
1257                 }
1258                 break;
1259             case "Opera":
1260                 $.Browser.vendor = $.BROWSERS.OPERA;
1261                 $.Browser.version = parseFloat( ver );
1262                 break;
1263         }
1264 
1265             // ignore '?' portion of query string
1266         var query = window.location.search.substring( 1 ),
1267             parts = query.split('&'),
1268             part,
1269             sep,
1270             i;
1271 
1272         for ( i = 0; i < parts.length; i++ ) {
1273             part = parts[ i ];
1274             sep  = part.indexOf( '=' );
1275 
1276             if ( sep > 0 ) {
1277                 URLPARAMS[ part.substring( 0, sep ) ] =
1278                     decodeURIComponent( part.substring( sep + 1 ) );
1279             }
1280         }
1281 
1282         //determine if this browser supports image alpha transparency
1283         $.Browser.alpha = !( 
1284             $.Browser.vendor == $.BROWSERS.IE || (
1285                 $.Browser.vendor == $.BROWSERS.CHROME && 
1286                 $.Browser.version < 2
1287             )
1288         );
1289 
1290     })();

1332     /**

1334      * @inner
1335      * @function
1336      * @param {XMLHttpRequest} xhr

1338      */
1339     function processDZIResponse( xhr, tilesUrl ) {
1340         var status,
1341             statusText,
1342             doc = null;
1343 
1344         if ( !xhr ) {
1345             throw new Error( $.getString( "Errors.Security" ) );
1346         } else if ( xhr.status !== 200 && xhr.status !== 0 ) {
1347             status     = xhr.status;
1348             statusText = ( status == 404 ) ? 
1349                 "Not Found" : 
1350                 xhr.statusText;
1351             throw new Error( $.getString( "Errors.Status", status, statusText ) );
1352         }
1353 
1354         if ( xhr.responseXML && xhr.responseXML.documentElement ) {
1355             doc = xhr.responseXML;
1356         } else if ( xhr.responseText ) {
1357             doc = parseXml( xhr.responseText );
1358         }
1359 
1360         return processDZIXml( doc, tilesUrl );
1361     };

1363     /**
1364      * @private
1365      * @inner
1366      * @function
1367      * @param {Document} xmlDoc
1368      * @param {String} tilesUrl
1369      */
1370     function processDZIXml( xmlDoc, tilesUrl ) {
1371 
1372         if ( !xmlDoc || !xmlDoc.documentElement ) {
1373             throw new Error( $.getString( "Errors.Xml" ) );
1374         }
1375 
1376         var root     = xmlDoc.documentElement,
1377             rootName = root.tagName;
1378 
1379         if ( rootName == "Image" ) {
1380             try {
1381                 return processDZI( root, tilesUrl );
1382             } catch ( e ) {
1383                 throw (e instanceof Error) ? 
1384                     e : 
1385                     new Error( $.getString("Errors.Dzi") );
1386             }
1387         } else if ( rootName == "Collection" ) {
1388             throw new Error( $.getString( "Errors.Dzc" ) );
1389         } else if ( rootName == "Error" ) {
1390             return processDZIError( root );
1391         }
1392 
1393         throw new Error( $.getString( "Errors.Dzi" ) );
1394     };

1396     /**
1397      * @private
1398      * @inner
1399      * @function
1400      * @param {Element} imageNode
1401      * @param {String} tilesUrl
1402      */
1403     function processDZI( imageNode, tilesUrl ) {
1404         var fileFormat    = imageNode.getAttribute( "Format" ),
1405             sizeNode      = imageNode.getElementsByTagName( "Size" )[ 0 ],
1406             dispRectNodes = imageNode.getElementsByTagName( "DisplayRect" ),
1407             width         = parseInt( sizeNode.getAttribute( "Width" ) ),
1408             height        = parseInt( sizeNode.getAttribute( "Height" ) ),
1409             tileSize      = parseInt( imageNode.getAttribute( "TileSize" ) ),
1410             tileOverlap   = parseInt( imageNode.getAttribute( "Overlap" ) ),
1411             dispRects     = [],
1412             dispRectNode,
1413             rectNode,
1414             i;
1415 
1416         if ( !imageFormatSupported( fileFormat ) ) {
1417             throw new Error(
1418                 $.getString( "Errors.ImageFormat", fileFormat.toUpperCase() )
1419             );
1420         }
1421 
1422         for ( i = 0; i < dispRectNodes.length; i++ ) {
1423             dispRectNode = dispRectNodes[ i ];
1424             rectNode     = dispRectNode.getElementsByTagName( "Rect" )[ 0 ];
1425 
1426             dispRects.push( new $.DisplayRect(
1427                 parseInt( rectNode.getAttribute( "X" ) ),
1428                 parseInt( rectNode.getAttribute( "Y" ) ),
1429                 parseInt( rectNode.getAttribute( "Width" ) ),
1430                 parseInt( rectNode.getAttribute( "Height" ) ),
1431                 0,  // ignore MinLevel attribute, bug in Deep Zoom Composer
1432                 parseInt( dispRectNode.getAttribute( "MaxLevel" ) )
1433             ));
1434         }
1435         return new $.DziTileSource(
1436             width, 
1437             height, 
1438             tileSize, 
1439             tileOverlap,
1440             tilesUrl, 
1441             fileFormat, 
1442             dispRects
1443         );

1526      * @param {Function} handler - Function to call when event is triggered.
1527      */
1528     addHandler: function( eventName, handler ) {
1529         var events = this.events[ eventName ];
1530         if( !events ){
1531             this.events[ eventName ] = events = [];
1532         }

1544     removeHandler: function( eventName, handler ) {

1546         //               - not actually being removed, we need to add the code
1547         //               - to do the removal ourselves. TODO
1548         var events = this.events[ eventName ];

1551         }

1556      * Retrive the list of all handlers registered for a given event.
1557      * @function
1558      * @param {String} eventName - Name of event to get handlers for.
1559      */
1560     getHandler: function( eventName ) {
1561         var events = this.events[ eventName ]; 
1562         if ( !events || !events.length ){ 
1563             return null; 
1564         }
1565         events = events.length === 1 ? 
1566             [ events[ 0 ] ] : 
1567             Array.apply( null, events );
1568         return function( source, args ) {
1569             var i, 
1570                 length = events.length;
1571             for ( i = 0; i < length; i++ ) {
1572                 if( events[ i ] ){
1573                     events[ i ]( source, args );
1574                 }
1575             }
1576         };
1577     },

1584      */
1585     raiseEvent: function( eventName, eventArgs ) {
1586         var handler = this.getHandler( eventName );
1587 
1588         if ( handler ) {
1589             if ( !eventArgs ) {
1590                 eventArgs = new Object();
1591             }
1592

1594         }

2058              delegate.capturing &&

2066                 event.target :

2152      */
2153     function onMouseDown( tracker, event ) {
2154         var event = $.getEvent( event ),
2155             delegate = THIS[ tracker.hash ];
2156 
2157         if ( event.button == 2 ) {
2158             return;
2159         }
2160 
2161         delegate.buttonDown = true;
2162 
2163         delegate.lastPoint = getMouseAbsolute( event );
2164         delegate.lastMouseDownPoint = delegate.lastPoint;
2165         delegate.lastMouseDownTime = +new Date();
2166 
2167         if ( tracker.pressHandler ) {
2168             try {
2169                 tracker.pressHandler( 
2170                     tracker, 
2171                     getMouseRelative( event, tracker.element )
2172                 );
2173             } catch (e) {
2174                 $.console.error(
2175                     "%s while executing press handler: %s", 
2176                     e.name,
2177                     e.message,
2178                     e
2179                 );
2180             }
2181         }
2182 
2183         if ( tracker.pressHandler || tracker.dragHandler ) {
2184             $.cancelEvent( event );
2185         }
2186 
2187         if ( !( $.Browser.vendor == $.BROWSERS.IE ) || !IS_CAPTURING ) {
2188             captureMouse( tracker );
2189             IS_CAPTURING = true;
2190             // reset to empty & add us
2191             CAPTURING = [ tracker ];     
2192         } else if ( $.Browser.vendor == $.BROWSERS.IE ) {
2193             // add us to the list
2194             CAPTURING.push( tracker );   
2195         }

2362     function onMouseWheelSpin( tracker, event ) {

3450 ///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
3451 // Schedulers provide the general engine for animation

3454 function scheduleUpdate( viewer, updateFunc, prevUpdateTime ){
3455     var currentTime,
3456         targetTime,
3457         deltaTime;
3458 
3459     if ( THIS[ viewer.hash ].animating ) {
3460         return window.setTimeout( function(){
3461             updateFunc( viewer );
3462         }, 1 );
3463     }
3464 
3465     currentTime     = +new Date();
3466     prevUpdateTime  = prevUpdateTime ? prevUpdateTime : currentTime;
3467     // 60 frames per second is ideal
3468     targetTime      = prevUpdateTime + 1000 / 60;
3469     deltaTime       = Math.max( 1, targetTime - currentTime );
3470     
3471     return window.setTimeout( function(){
3472         updateFunc( viewer );
3473     }, deltaTime );
3474 };

3484 function beginControlsAutoHide( viewer ) {

3486         return;

3495     }, viewer.controlsFadeDelay );

3499 //determines if fade animation is done or continues the animation
3500 function updateControlsFade( viewer ) {
3501     var currentTime,
3502         deltaTime,
3503         opacity,
3504         i;
3505     if ( viewer.controlsShouldFade ) {
3506         currentTime = new Date().getTime();
3507         deltaTime = currentTime - viewer.controlsFadeBeginTime;
3508         opacity = 1.0 - deltaTime / viewer.controlsFadeLength;
3509 
3510         opacity = Math.min( 1.0, opacity );
3511         opacity = Math.max( 0.0, opacity );
3512 
3513         for ( i = viewer.controls.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
3514             viewer.controls[ i ].setOpacity( opacity );
3515         }
3516 
3517         if ( opacity > 0 ) {
3518             // fade again
3519             scheduleControlsFade( viewer ); 
3520         }
3521     }
3522 };

3528     for ( i = viewer.controls.length - 1; i >= 0; i-- ) {

3619 function updateMulti( viewer ) {
3620 
3621     var beginTime;
3622 
3623     if ( !viewer.source ) {
3624         return;
3625     }
3626 
3627     beginTime = +new Date();
3628     updateOnce( viewer );
3629     scheduleUpdate( viewer, arguments.callee, beginTime );
3630 };
3631 
3632 function updateOnce( viewer ) {
3633 
3634     var containerSize,
3635         animated;
3636 
3637     if ( !viewer.source ) {
3638         return;
3639     }
3640 
3641     //viewer.profiler.beginUpdate();
3642 
3643     containerSize = $.getElementSize( viewer.container );
3644     if ( !containerSize.equals( THIS[ viewer.hash ].prevContainerSize ) ) {
3645         // maintain image position
3646         viewer.viewport.resize( containerSize, true ); 
3647         THIS[ viewer.hash ].prevContainerSize = containerSize;
3648         viewer.raiseEvent( "resize" );
3649     }
3650 
3651     animated = viewer.viewport.update();
3652     if ( !THIS[ viewer.hash ].animating && animated ) {
3653         viewer.raiseEvent( "animationstart" );
3654         abortControlsAutoHide( viewer );
3655     }
3656 
3657     if ( animated ) {
3658         viewer.drawer.update();
3659         viewer.raiseEvent( "animation" );
3660     } else if ( THIS[ viewer.hash ].forceRedraw || viewer.drawer.needsUpdate() ) {
3661         viewer.drawer.update();
3662         THIS[ viewer.hash ].forceRedraw = false;
3663     } 
3664 
3665     if ( THIS[ viewer.hash ].animating && !animated ) {
3666         viewer.raiseEvent( "animationfinish" );
3667 
3668         if ( !THIS[ viewer.hash ].mouseInside ) {
3669             beginControlsAutoHide( viewer );
3670         }
3671     }
3672 
3673     THIS[ viewer.hash ].animating = animated;
3674 
3675     //viewer.profiler.endUpdate();
3676 };

4599 function updateFade( button ) {
4600     var currentTime,
4601         deltaTime,
4602         opacity;
4603 
4604     if ( button.shouldFade ) {
4605         currentTime = +new Date();
4606         deltaTime   = currentTime - button.fadeBeginTime;
4607         opacity     = 1.0 - deltaTime / button.fadeLength;
4608         opacity     = Math.min( 1.0, opacity );
4609         opacity     = Math.max( 0.0, opacity );
4610         
4611         $.setElementOpacity( button.imgGroup, opacity, true );
4612         if ( opacity > 0 ) {
4613             // fade again
4614             scheduleFade( button );
4615         }
4616     }
4617 };

4621     button.fadeBeginTime = +new Date() + button.fadeDelay;
4622     window.setTimeout( function(){ 
4623         scheduleFade( button );
4624     }, button.fadeDelay );
4625 };

4628     button.shouldFade = false;
4629     $.setElementOpacity( button.imgGroup, 1.0, true );

4638

4640          button.currentState == $.ButtonState.GROUP ) {
4641         button.imgHover.style.visibility = "";
4642         button.currentState = $.ButtonState.HOVER;
4643     }
4644 
4645     if ( newState >= $.ButtonState.DOWN && 
4646          button.currentState == $.ButtonState.HOVER ) {
4647         button.imgDown.style.visibility = "";
4648         button.currentState = $.ButtonState.DOWN;
4649     }
4650 };

4655          button.currentState == $.ButtonState.DOWN ) {
4656         button.imgDown.style.visibility = "hidden";
4657         button.currentState = $.ButtonState.HOVER;
4658     }
4659 
4660     if ( newState <= $.ButtonState.GROUP && 
4661          button.currentState == $.ButtonState.HOVER ) {
4662         button.imgHover.style.visibility = "hidden";
4663         button.currentState = $.ButtonState.GROUP;
4664     }
4665

4667          button.currentState == $.ButtonState.GROUP ) {
4668         beginFading( button );
4669         button.currentState = $.ButtonState.REST;

5002         this.start.time   = this.current.time;
5003         this.target.value = target;
5004         this.target.time  = this.start.time + 1000 * this.animationTime;
5005     },
5006 
5007     /**
5008      * @function
5009      * @param {Number} delta
5010      */
5011     shiftBy: function( delta ) {
5012         this.start.value  += delta;
5013         this.target.value += delta;
5014     },
5015 
5016     /**
5017      * @function
5018      */
5019     update: function() {
5020         this.current.time  = new Date().getTime();
5021         this.current.value = (this.current.time >= this.target.time) ? 
5022             this.target.value :
5023             this.start.value + 
5024                 ( this.target.value - this.start.value ) *
5025                 transform( 
5026                     this.springStiffness, 
5027                     ( this.current.time - this.start.time ) / 
5028                     ( this.target.time  - this.start.time )
5029                 );
5030     }
5031 }
5032 
5033 /**
5034  * @private
5035  */
5036 function transform( stiffness, x ) {
5037     return ( 1.0 - Math.exp( stiffness * -x ) ) / 
5038         ( 1.0 - Math.exp( -stiffness ) );
5039 };

5596     /**

5599      * the local cache to optimize user experience in certain cases. Because
5600      * the number of parallel image loads is configurable, if too many images
5601      * are currently being loaded, the request will be ignored.  Since by 
5602      * default drawer.imageLoaderLimit is 0, the native browser parallel 
5603      * image loading policy will be used.
5604      * @method
5605      * @param {String} src - The url of the image to load.
5606      * @param {Function} callback - The function that will be called with the
5607      *      Image object as the only parameter, whether on 'load' or on 'abort'.
5608      *      For now this means the callback is expected to distinguish between
5609      *      error and success conditions by inspecting the Image object.
5610      * @return {Boolean} loading - Wheter the request was submitted or ignored 
5611      *      based on OpenSeadragon.DEFAULT_SETTINGS.imageLoaderLimit.
5612      */
5613     loadImage: function( src, callback ) {
5614         var _this = this,
5615             loading = false,
5616             image,
5617             jobid,
5618             complete;
5619         
5620         if ( !this.imageLoaderLimit || 
5621               this.downloading < this.imageLoaderLimit ) {
5622             
5623             this.downloading++;
5624 
5625             image = new Image();
5626 
5627             complete = function( imagesrc ){
5628                 _this.downloading--;
5629                 if (typeof ( callback ) == "function") {
5630                     try {
5631                         callback( image );
5632                     } catch ( e ) {
5633                         $.console.error(
5634                             "%s while executing %s callback: %s", 
5635                             e.name,
5636                             src,
5637                             e.message,
5638                             e
5639                         );
5640                     }
5641                 }
5642             };

5644             image.onload = function(){
5645                 finishLoadingImage( image, complete, true );
5646             };
5647 
5648             image.onabort = image.onerror = function(){
5649                 finishLoadingImage( image, complete, false );
5650             };
5651 
5652             jobid = window.setTimeout( function(){
5653                 finishLoadingImage( image, complete, false, jobid );
5654             }, TIMEOUT );
5655 
5656             loading   = true;
5657             image.src = src;
5658         }
5659 
5660         return loading;
5661     }

5860 function updateTile( drawer, drawLevel, haveDrawn, x, y, level, levelOpacity, levelVisibility, viewportCenter, numberOfTiles, currentTime, best){
5861

5921 function getTile( x, y, level, tileSource, tilesMatrix, time, numTiles, normHeight ) {
5922     var xMod,
5923         yMod,
5924         bounds,
5925         exists,
5926         url,
5927         tile;
5928 
5929     if ( !tilesMatrix[ level ] ) {
5930         tilesMatrix[ level ] = {};
5931     }
5932     if ( !tilesMatrix[ level ][ x ] ) {
5933         tilesMatrix[ level ][ x ] = {};
5934     }
5935 
5936     if ( !tilesMatrix[ level ][ x ][ y ] ) {
5937         xMod    = ( numTiles.x + ( x % numTiles.x ) ) % numTiles.x;
5938         yMod    = ( numTiles.y + ( y % numTiles.y ) ) % numTiles.y;
5939         bounds  = tileSource.getTileBounds( level, xMod, yMod );
5940         exists  = tileSource.tileExists( level, xMod, yMod );
5941         url     = tileSource.getTileUrl( level, xMod, yMod );
5942 
5943         bounds.x += 1.0 * ( x - xMod ) / numTiles.x;
5944         bounds.y += normHeight * ( y - yMod ) / numTiles.y;
5945 
5946         tilesMatrix[ level ][ x ][ y ] = new $.Tile(
5947             level, 
5948             x, 
5949             y, 
5950             bounds, 
5951             exists, 
5952             url
5953         );
5954     }
5955 
5956     tile = tilesMatrix[ level ][ x ][ y ];
5957     tile.lastTouchTime = time;
5958 
5959     return tile;
5960 };

5972 function onTileLoad( drawer, tile, time, image ) {
5973     var insertionIndex,
5974         cutoff,
5975         worstTile,
5976         worstTime,
5977         worstLevel,
5978         worstTileIndex,
5979         prevTile,
5980         prevTime,
5981         prevLevel,
5982         i;
5983 
5984     tile.loading = false;
5985 
5986     if ( drawer.midUpdate ) {
5987         $.console.warn( "Tile load callback in middle of drawing routine." );
5988         return;
5989     } else if ( !image ) {
5990         $.console.log( "Tile %s failed to load: %s", tile, tile.url );
5991         tile.exists = false;
5992         return;
5993     } else if ( time < drawer.lastResetTime ) {
5994         $.console.log( "Ignoring tile %s loaded before reset: %s", tile, tile.url );
5995         return;
5996     }
5997 
5998     tile.loaded = true;
5999     tile.image  = image;
6000 
6001     insertionIndex = drawer.tilesLoaded.length;
6002 
6003     if ( drawer.tilesLoaded.length >= drawer.maxImageCacheCount ) {
6004         cutoff = Math.ceil( Math.log( drawer.source.tileSize ) / Math.log( 2 ) );
6005 
6006         worstTile       = null;
6007         worstTileIndex  = -1;
6008 
6009         for ( i = drawer.tilesLoaded.length - 1; i >= 0; i-- ) {
6010             prevTile = drawer.tilesLoaded[ i ];
6011 
6012             if ( prevTile.level <= drawer.cutoff || prevTile.beingDrawn ) {
6013                 continue;
6014             } else if ( !worstTile ) {
6015                 worstTile       = prevTile;
6016                 worstTileIndex  = i;
6017                 continue;
6018             }
6019 
6020             prevTime    = prevTile.lastTouchTime;
6021             worstTime   = worstTile.lastTouchTime;
6022             prevLevel   = prevTile.level;
6023             worstLevel  = worstTile.level;
6024 
6025             if ( prevTime < worstTime || 
6026                ( prevTime == worstTime && prevLevel > worstLevel ) ) {
6027                 worstTile       = prevTile;
6028                 worstTileIndex  = i;
6029             }
6030         }
6031 
6032         if ( worstTile && worstTileIndex >= 0 ) {
6033             worstTile.unload();
6034             insertionIndex = worstTileIndex;
6035         }
6036     }
6037 
6038     drawer.tilesLoaded[ insertionIndex ] = tile;
6039     drawer.updateAgain = true;
6040 };

6043 function positionTile( tile, overlap, viewport, viewportCenter, levelVisibility ){
6044     var boundsTL     = tile.bounds.getTopLeft(),
6045         boundsSize   = tile.bounds.getSize(),
6046         positionC    = viewport.pixelFromPoint( boundsTL, true ),
6047         positionT    = viewport.pixelFromPoint( boundsTL, false ),
6048         sizeC        = viewport.deltaPixelsFromPoints( boundsSize, true ),
6049         sizeT        = viewport.deltaPixelsFromPoints( boundsSize, false ),
6050         tileCenter   = positionT.plus( sizeT.divide( 2 ) ),
6051         tileDistance = viewportCenter.distanceTo( tileCenter );
6052 
6053     if ( !overlap ) {
6054         sizeC = sizeC.plus( new $.Point( 1, 1 ) );
6055     }
6056 
6057     tile.position   = positionC;
6058     tile.size       = sizeC;
6059     tile.distance   = tileDistance;
6060     tile.visibility = levelVisibility;

6064 function blendTile( drawer, tile, x, y, level, levelOpacity, currentTime ){
6065     var blendTimeMillis = 1000 * drawer.blendTime,
6066         deltaTime,
6067         opacity;
6068 
6069     if ( !tile.blendStart ) {
6070         tile.blendStart = currentTime;
6071     }
6072 
6073     deltaTime   = currentTime - tile.blendStart;
6074     opacity     = Math.min( 1, deltaTime / blendTimeMillis );
6075     
6076     if ( drawer.alwaysBlend ) {
6077         opacity *= levelOpacity;
6078     }
6079 
6080     tile.opacity = opacity;
6081 
6082     drawer.lastDrawn.push( tile );
6083 
6084     if ( opacity == 1 ) {
6085         setCoverage( drawer.coverage, level, x, y, true );
6086     } else if ( deltaTime < blendTimeMillis ) {
6087         return true;
6088     }
6089 
6090     return false;
6091 };

6099 /**
6100  * @private
6101  * @inner
6102  * Returns true if the given tile provides coverage to lower-level tiles of
6103  * lower resolution representing the same content. If neither x nor y is
6104  * given, returns true if the entire visible level provides coverage.
6105  * 
6106  * Note that out-of-bounds tiles provide coverage in this sense, since
6107  * there's no content that they would need to cover. Tiles at non-existent
6108  * levels that are within the image bounds, however, do not.
6109  */
6110 function providesCoverage( coverage, level, x, y ) {
6111     var rows,
6112         cols,
6113         i, j;
6114 
6115     if ( !coverage[ level ] ) {
6116         return false;
6117     }
6118 
6119     if ( x === undefined || y === undefined ) {
6120         rows = coverage[ level ];
6121         for ( i in rows ) {
6122             if ( rows.hasOwnProperty( i ) ) {
6123                 cols = rows[ i ];
6124                 for ( j in cols ) {
6125                     if ( cols.hasOwnProperty( j ) && !cols[ j ] ) {
6126                         return false;
6127                     }
6128                 }
6129             }
6130         }
6131 
6132         return true;
6133     }
6134 
6135     return (
6136         coverage[ level ][ x] === undefined ||
6137         coverage[ level ][ x ][ y ] === undefined ||
6138         coverage[ level ][ x ][ y ] === true
6139     );
6140 };
6141 
6142 /**
6143  * @private
6144  * @inner
6145  * Returns true if the given tile is completely covered by higher-level
6146  * tiles of higher resolution representing the same content. If neither x
6147  * nor y is given, returns true if the entire visible level is covered.
6148  */
6149 function isCovered( coverage, level, x, y ) {
6150     if ( x === undefined || y === undefined ) {
6151         return providesCoverage( coverage, level + 1 );
6152     } else {
6153         return (
6154              providesCoverage( coverage, level + 1, 2 * x, 2 * y ) &&
6155              providesCoverage( coverage, level + 1, 2 * x, 2 * y + 1 ) &&
6156              providesCoverage( coverage, level + 1, 2 * x + 1, 2 * y ) &&
6157              providesCoverage( coverage, level + 1, 2 * x + 1, 2 * y + 1 )
6158         );
6159     }
6160 };

6162 /**
6163  * @private
6164  * @inner
6165  * Sets whether the given tile provides coverage or not.
6166  */
6167 function setCoverage( coverage, level, x, y, covers ) {
6168     if ( !coverage[ level ] ) {
6169         $.console.warn(
6170             "Setting coverage for a tile before its level's coverage has been reset: %s", 
6171             level
6172         );
6173         return;
6174     }
6175 
6176     if ( !coverage[ level ][ x ] ) {
6177         coverage[ level ][ x ] = {};
6178     }
6179 
6180     coverage[ level ][ x ][ y ] = covers;
6181 };

6188  * routine, coverage for every visible tile should be explicitly set. 
6189  */
6190 function resetCoverage( coverage, level ) {
6191     coverage[ level ] = {};
6192 };

6194 /**
6195  * @private

6198  * a z-index based on the order they are added to the Drawer.

6200 function getOverlayIndex( overlays, element ) {
6201     var i;
6202     for ( i = overlays.length - 1; i >= 0; i-- ) {
6203         if ( overlays[ i ].element == element ) {
6204             return i;
6205         }
6206     }
6207

6211 /**
6212  * @private
6213  * @inner
6214  * Determines whether the 'last best' tile for the area is better than the 
6215  * tile in question.
6216  */
6217 function compareTiles( previousBest, tile ) {
6218     if ( !previousBest ) {
6219         return tile;
6220     }
6221 
6222     if ( tile.visibility > previousBest.visibility ) {
6223         return tile;
6224     } else if ( tile.visibility == previousBest.visibility ) {
6225         if ( tile.distance < previousBest.distance ) {
6226             return tile;
6227         }
6228     }
6229 
6230     return previousBest;
6231 };

6444             bounds,
6445             newZoomPixel,
6446             deltaZoomPixels,
6447             deltaZoomPoints;
6448 
6449         if ( current ) {
6450             return centerCurrent;
6451         } else if ( !this.zoomPoint ) {
6452             return centerTarget;
6453         }
6454 
6455         oldZoomPixel = this.pixelFromPoint(this.zoomPoint, true);
6456 
6457         zoom    = this.getZoom();
6458         width   = 1.0 / zoom;
6459         height  = width / this.getAspectRatio();
6460         bounds  = new $.Rect(
6461             centerCurrent.x - width / 2.0,
6462             centerCurrent.y - height / 2.0, 
6463             width, 
6464             height
6465         );
6466 
6467         newZoomPixel    = this.zoomPoint.minus(
6468             bounds.getTopLeft()
6469         ).times(
6470             this.containerSize.x / bounds.width
6471         );
6472         deltaZoomPixels = newZoomPixel.minus( oldZoomPixel );
6473         deltaZoomPoints = deltaZoomPixels.divide( this.containerSize.x * zoom );
6474 
6475         return centerTarget.plus( deltaZoomPoints );
6476     },
6477 
6478     /**
6479      * @function
6480      */
6481     getZoom: function( current ) {
6482         if ( current ) {
6483             return this.zoomSpring.current.value;
6484         } else {
6485             return this.zoomSpring.target.value;
6486         }
6487     },

6490     /**
6491      * @function
6492      */
6493     applyConstraints: function( immediately ) {
6494         var actualZoom = this.getZoom(),
6495             constrainedZoom = Math.max(
6496                 Math.min( actualZoom, this.getMaxZoom() ), 
6497                 this.getMinZoom()
6498             ),
6499             bounds,
6500             horizontalThreshold,
6501             verticalThreshold,
6502             left,
6503             right,
6504             top,
6505             bottom,
6506             dx = 0,
6507             dy = 0;
6508 
6509         if ( actualZoom != constrainedZoom ) {
6510             this.zoomTo( constrainedZoom, this.zoomPoint, immediately );
6511         }
6512 
6513         bounds = this.getBounds();
6514 
6515         horizontalThreshold = this.visibilityRatio * bounds.width;
6516         verticalThreshold   = this.visibilityRatio * bounds.height;
6517 
6518         left   = bounds.x + bounds.width;
6519         right  = 1 - bounds.x;
6520         top    = bounds.y + bounds.height;
6521         bottom = this.contentHeight - bounds.y;
6522 
6523         if ( this.wrapHorizontal ) {
6524             //do nothing
6525         } else if ( left < horizontalThreshold ) {
6526             dx = horizontalThreshold - left;
6527         } else if ( right < horizontalThreshold ) {
6528             dx = right - horizontalThreshold;
6529         }
6530 
6531         if ( this.wrapVertical ) {
6532             //do nothing
6533         } else if ( top < verticalThreshold ) {
6534             dy = verticalThreshold - top;
6535         } else if ( bottom < verticalThreshold ) {
6536             dy = bottom - verticalThreshold;
6537         }
6538 
6539         if ( dx || dy ) {
6540             bounds.x += dx;
6541             bounds.y += dy;
6542             this.fitBounds( bounds, immediately );
6543         }
6544     },
6545 
6546     /**
6547      * @function
6548      * @param {Boolean} immediately
6549      */
6550     ensureVisible: function( immediately ) {
6551         this.applyConstraints( immediately );
6552     },

6554     /**
6555      * @function
6556      * @param {OpenSeadragon.Rect} bounds
6557      * @param {Boolean} immediately
6558      */
6559     fitBounds: function( bounds, immediately ) {
6560         var aspect = this.getAspectRatio(),
6561             center = bounds.getCenter(),
6562             newBounds = new $.Rect(
6563                 bounds.x, 
6564                 bounds.y, 
6565                 bounds.width, 
6566                 bounds.height
6567             ),
6568             oldBounds,
6569             oldZoom,
6570             newZoom,
6571             referencePoint;
6572 
6573         if ( newBounds.getAspectRatio() >= aspect ) {
6574             newBounds.height = bounds.width / aspect;
6575             newBounds.y      = center.y - newBounds.height / 2;
6576         } else {
6577             newBounds.width = bounds.height * aspect;
6578             newBounds.x     = center.x - newBounds.width / 2;
6579         }
6580 
6581         this.panTo( this.getCenter( true ), true );
6582         this.zoomTo( this.getZoom( true ), null, true );
6583 
6584         oldBounds = this.getBounds();
6585         oldZoom   = this.getZoom();
6586         newZoom   = 1.0 / newBounds.width;
6587         if ( newZoom == oldZoom || newBounds.width == oldBounds.width ) {
6588             this.panTo( center, immediately );
6589             return;
6590         }
6591 
6592         referencePoint = oldBounds.getTopLeft().times( 
6593             this.containerSize.x / oldBounds.width 
6594         ).minus(
6595             newBounds.getTopLeft().times( 
6596                 this.containerSize.x / newBounds.width 
6597             )
6598         ).divide(
6599             this.containerSize.x / oldBounds.width - 
6600             this.containerSize.x / newBounds.width
6601         );
6602 
6603 
6604         this.zoomTo( newZoom, referencePoint, immediately );
6605     },
6606 
6607     /**
6608      * @function
6609      * @param {Boolean} immediately
6610      */
6611     goHome: function( immediately ) {
6612         var center = this.getCenter();
6613 
6614         if ( this.wrapHorizontal ) {
6615             center.x = ( 1 + ( center.x % 1 ) ) % 1;
6616             this.centerSpringX.resetTo( center.x );
6617             this.centerSpringX.update();
6618         }
6619 
6620         if ( this.wrapVertical ) {
6621             center.y = (
6622                 this.contentHeight + ( center.y % this.contentHeight )
6623             ) % this.contentHeight;
6624             this.centerSpringY.resetTo( center.y );
6625             this.centerSpringY.update();
6626         }
6627 
6628         this.fitBounds( this.homeBounds, immediately );
6629     },

6635      */
6636     panBy: function( delta, immediately ) {
6637         var center = new $.Point(
6638             this.centerSpringX.target.value,
6639             this.centerSpringY.target.value
6640         );
6641         this.panTo( center.plus( delta ), immediately );
6642     },

6644     /**
6645      * @function
6646      * @param {OpenSeadragon.Point} center
6647      * @param {Boolean} immediately
6648      */
6649     panTo: function( center, immediately ) {
6650         if ( immediately ) {
6651             this.centerSpringX.resetTo( center.x );
6652             this.centerSpringY.resetTo( center.y );
6653         } else {
6654             this.centerSpringX.springTo( center.x );
6655             this.centerSpringY.springTo( center.y );
6656         }
6657     },

6659     /**
6660      * @function
6661      */
6662     zoomBy: function( factor, refPoint, immediately ) {
6663         this.zoomTo( this.zoomSpring.target.value * factor, refPoint, immediately );
6664     },

6666     /**
6667      * @function
6668      */
6669     zoomTo: function( zoom, refPoint, immediately ) {
6670 
6671         if ( immediately ) {
6672             this.zoomSpring.resetTo( zoom );
6673         } else {        
6674             this.zoomSpring.springTo( zoom );
6675         }
6676 
6677         this.zoomPoint = refPoint instanceof $.Point ? 
6678             refPoint : 
6679             null;
6680     },

6682     /**
6683      * @function
6684      */
6685     resize: function( newContainerSize, maintain ) {
6686         var oldBounds = this.getBounds(),
6687             newBounds = oldBounds,
6688             widthDeltaFactor = newContainerSize.x / this.containerSize.x;
6689 
6690         this.containerSize = new $.Point(
6691             newContainerSize.x, 
6692             newContainerSize.y
6693         );
6694 
6695         if (maintain) {
6696             newBounds.width  = oldBounds.width * widthDeltaFactor;
6697             newBounds.height = newBounds.width / this.getAspectRatio();
6698         }
6699 
6700         this.fitBounds( newBounds, true );
6701     },
6702 
6703     /**
6704      * @function
6705      */
6706     update: function() {
6707         var oldCenterX = this.centerSpringX.current.value,
6708             oldCenterY = this.centerSpringY.current.value,
6709             oldZoom    = this.zoomSpring.current.value,
6710             oldZoomPixel,
6711             newZoomPixel,
6712             deltaZoomPixels,
6713             deltaZoomPoints;
6714 
6715         if (this.zoomPoint) {
6716             oldZoomPixel = this.pixelFromPoint( this.zoomPoint, true );
6717         }
6718 
6719         this.zoomSpring.update();
6720 
6721         if (this.zoomPoint && this.zoomSpring.current.value != oldZoom) {
6722             newZoomPixel    = this.pixelFromPoint( this.zoomPoint, true );
6723             deltaZoomPixels = newZoomPixel.minus( oldZoomPixel );
6724             deltaZoomPoints = this.deltaPointsFromPixels( deltaZoomPixels, true );
6725 
6726             this.centerSpringX.shiftBy( deltaZoomPoints.x );
6727             this.centerSpringY.shiftBy( deltaZoomPoints.y );
6728         } else {
6729             this.zoomPoint = null;
6730         }
6731 
6732         this.centerSpringX.update();
6733         this.centerSpringY.update();
6734 
6735         return this.centerSpringX.current.value != oldCenterX ||
6736             this.centerSpringY.current.value != oldCenterY ||
6737             this.zoomSpring.current.value != oldZoom;
6738     },

6742      * @function
6743      */
6744     deltaPixelsFromPoints: function( deltaPoints, current ) {

6746             this.containerSize.x * this.getZoom( current )
6747         );
6748     },

6750     /**
6751      * @function
6752      */
6753     deltaPointsFromPixels: function( deltaPixels, current ) {

6756         );

6759     /**
6760      * @function
6761      */
6762     pixelFromPoint: function( point, current ) {
6763         var bounds = this.getBounds( current );
6764         return point.minus(
6765             bounds.getTopLeft()
6766         ).times(
6767             this.containerSize.x / bounds.width
6768         );
6769     },

6771     /**
6772      * @function
6773      */
6774     pointFromPixel: function( pixel, current ) {
6775         var bounds = this.getBounds( current );
6776         return pixel.divide(
6777             this.containerSize.x / bounds.width
6778         ).plus(
6779             bounds.getTopLeft()
6780         );
6781     }
